article.headline: Vermont 84, Quinnipiac 79
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. -- Mike Trimboli scored 24 points on 7-for-7 shooting from the floor as Vermont defeated Quinnipiac 84-79 on Sunday. Marqus Blakely and Maurice Joseph also contributed 16 and 15 points, respectively, for Vermont (6-3). Quinnipiac trailed by 20 points with 7:18 remaining in regulation. A 14-2 run cut the deficit to eight by the 4:17 mark. A pair of three-pointers by James Feldeine made it 82-79 with nine seconds left. But Joey Accaoui's two free throws for Vermont with six seconds remaining put the game out of reach. Feldeine scored 26 points and Justin Rutty added a double-double of 22 points and 10 rebounds for Quinnipiac (6-4). Vermont outshot Quinnipiac from the floor, 50 percent to 48.4 percent, as well as 33.3 percent to 30 percent from three-point range. The Bobcats outrebounded the Catamounts, 34-31, and made a season-high 16 steals.
